  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To increase community engagement with service providers and policy makers for better service delivery and budget executionTo increase the demand for better public services in 10 districts in Zambia by providing 900 community members with technical support to monitor services and hold decision-makers to account. By 2013, approximately 1.7 million Zambians in the 10 districts will benefit from the improved quality of health and education, water and sanitation, agriculture, and social protection services.</narrative>
